g.text: Cargo Container Door: Before you stands a cargo container. Just one of many in the yard.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You do? Because I don't."
Rhetoric: Why are you even trying to open a door with rhetoric?
You: "Using my body over my wits."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Now is not the time to get philosophical, detective. You can do that after hours."
Cargo Container Door: Variable["TASK.interview_union_boss"] == true and Variable["TASK.ask_for_help_from_the_harbour"] == false and Variable["TASK.interview_union_boss_done"] == false
Variable["TASK.interview_union_boss"] == true and Variable["TASK.ask_for_help_from_the_harbour"] == false and Variable["TASK.interview_union_boss_done"] == false
Kim Kitsuragi: "We're not here to interact with containers -- we're here to interview the Union boss."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We're not here to interact with containers -- we're here to talk to the Union, right?"
You: "Mark my words -- there's someone rich buzzing away inside!"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't hear anything." The lieutenant cups one of his ears.
Physical Instrument: How'd he get in front? Little slimeball...
You: "Because getting physical wasn't an option!"
You: Nothing more to do here for now. [Leave.]
You: (Inspect the container.) "Maybe there's contraband in there?"
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant considers this for a moment. "There may very well be, but we're not here to look for that."
You: "No, it's totally different. I don't want to paint it. I'm just *drawn* to it."
Kim Kitsuragi: "There are a million containers here. Why are you fixating on this one?"
Rhetoric: No one needs you. Go away.
You: "If there's someone in there, I'd like to talk to you."
You: "It was hanging from the crane."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You just picked one out, because you wanted to interact with a cargo container."
Cargo Container Door: Variable["TASK.ask_for_help_from_the_harbour"] == true and Variable["TASK.interview_union_boss"] == false and Variable["TASK.ask_for_help_from_the_harbour_done"] == false

Kim Kitsuragi: "We're not here to interact with containers -- we're here to get the body down from the tree."
Savoir Faire: Seems like it. You're still hanging with this fool? Something isn't right...
Cargo Container Door: You attempt to turn the handle, to no avail. The doors seem to be mechanically locked.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant sighs. "Is this like your thing with that wall again?"
You: "Khm-khm..." (Clear your throat, knock on the door.) "Hi, it's Savvy here, Savvy with two v's, I'm on the list. The guest list."
Cargo Container Door: At first your knock rings hollow on the door -- and then...
Perception (Hearing): The knock produces a hollow ring of metal. Doesn't sound like there's anything inside the container.
You: "Maybe? I can't tell. I think we should investigate further."
Rhetoric: Aaaaand as it's always been -- it's impossible to open a container with rhetoric. Maybe you're losing your mind?
Savoir Faire: Step aside, rank and file, Savvy's at the top of the VIP list here. That's right -- out of the way!
Rhetoric: Despite the dirt that surrounds and trails you, a beacon of light emerges from deep within you.
You: "Hello, is there anybody in there?"
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant nods. "Are you satisfied, detective?"
Rhetoric: Who understands anything you do?
Kim Kitsuragi: The smile disappears. "You can't be serious."
The lieutenant's smile disappears. "You can't be serious."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Damn it, now you've got *me* curious... this is *not* what we came to the harbour for."
Esprit de Corps: To your left, the lieutenant considers your actions -- with some puzzlement.
You: "Lieutenant, I think there's something *special* about this container..."
Cargo Container Door: You're back before the cargo container. Its draw has not lessened since you were last here. If anything, it seems to have grown slightly.
You: Persuade the door to open.
Cargo Container Door: The door does not respond to your advances. Is it possible that it seems somehow *more* closed than before?
Savoir Faire: That's a very good question considering you have Savvy around -- the ultimate VIP.
Cargo Container Door: Just like that, you hear a click. Then a rattle. Some mechanism unlocks itself inside the door.
Mega Rich Light-Bending Guy: From deep within the container, a voice: "Ahoy! Come on in!"
Savoir Faire: Thank you, thank you. Now, are you ready? It's time to *make our entrance*.
Rhetoric: You've got to dance with the one that brought you, detective.
Cargo Container Door: IsKimHere() or Variable["cargo.container_flattered"]
Kim Kitsuragi: "Why are you what?" The lieutenant looks startled.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Satisfied, detective?" A wry smile crosses the lieutenant's face.
You: "That's because you're not *tuned in*. Perks of being a hustler. You'll see -- I'll be rolling in money soon."
You: "I don't know, Kim, it just *feels* special."
Cargo Container Door: The door stands silent.
You: "C'mon, don't shut me out. Let me in."
Cargo Container Door: The mundaneness of the situation does not seem to affect the container in the slightest.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's a cargo container, detective. Just like all the others." He doesn't even look at it.
Cargo Container Door: The container door appears unmoved by your attempt at flattery.
Suggestion: A tough nut to crack, for sure. But the strongest containers often have the softest hearts.
You: "You're a fine piece of engineering, do you know that?"
Cargo Container Door: The door does not respond to your advances. Is it possible that it seems somehow *more* closed than before?
Cargo Container Door: The door seems to be locked. Conclusively.
Inland Empire: Why does this situation feel so familiar? Do you have a history of propositioning inanimate objects?
You: "Nevermind, I have better things to do." [Leave.]
You: "It's just another day, another cop and another container."
Physical Instrument: Have I been summoned?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Because what wasn't an option?" The lieutenant looks startled.
You: "What's the matter, honey? You shy?"
